        {
          "type": "final",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "T001 and T002 split the schema migration into two ordered tasks: T001 makes schema_version 3 a hard error, while T002 updates the actual dry-check config to schema_version 4. Because CN-05 requires non-v4 configs to fail hard, the intermediate state after T001 is unexecutable until T002 lands. Make the loader switch and config migration atomic, or explicitly combine them into one task/commit.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "track/items/dry-gate-opt-in-2026-06-21/plan.md",
              "line": 18,
              "category": "infeasibility"
            },
            {
              "message": "CN-04 covers enabled=true behavior for both DryCheckApprovalService::check_approved and FixpointResolveInteractor, but the coverage map lists only T005/T006. Those tasks cover the approval interactor and wiring, while the FixpointResolveInteractor preservation path is in T007/T008 and tested by T011. As written, the generated coverage/spec task list can miss the fixpoint half of CN-04.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "track/items/dry-gate-opt-in-2026-06-21/task-coverage.json",
              "line": 23,
              "category": "factual error"
            }
          ],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:35e1af381198d66e09364b4213ba5589e8c9886822935c62cc07d0168354d89a",
          "at": "2026-06-21T07:41:26Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "final",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "AC-04 is a CLI-level acceptance criterion for `sotp dry check-approved` with `enabled: true`, but its task coverage omits T006, the composition task that wires the CLI path to pass `DryCheckConfig` into `DryCheckApprovalInteractor::new`. This means the plan can mark the acceptance criterion covered by the interactor change and tests while the actual command entry point remains unwired, unlike the analogous `enabled: false` AC-03 coverage that includes T006. Add T006 to AC-04 coverage so the enabled=true CLI behavior is covered end to end.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "track/items/dry-gate-opt-in-2026-06-21/task-coverage.json",
              "line": 31,
              "category": "task_coverage_gap"
            }
          ],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:6acafd85315de7191985b7f99b6f3c01ac52c4a55a257c88d13af70ad3c9afe0",
          "at": "2026-06-21T07:46:55Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "final",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "The implementation plan places the disabled-gate short-circuit inside `DryCheckApprovalInteractor::check_approved` and `FixpointResolveInteractor::resolve`, after the callers have already had to build dry fragment refs/fingerprints to call those APIs. That still runs DRY diff/corpus preparation with `enabled: false`, contradicting GO-02/CN-02's requirement that DRY detection/gate work not execute. The plan needs a composition-level early check or a lazy/optional refs interface before dry fragment construction.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "track/items/dry-gate-opt-in-2026-06-21/impl-plan.json",
              "line": 30,
              "category": "contradiction"
            },
            {
              "message": "CN-04 covers both `DryCheckApprovalService::check_approved` and `FixpointResolveInteractor` preserving enabled=true behavior, but the coverage map includes only T011 for the Fixpoint side and omits T010, the task that tests DryCheckApproval enabled=true coverage-absent and violation behavior. This makes the constraint coverage incomplete and inconsistent with AC-04, which correctly maps T010.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "track/items/dry-gate-opt-in-2026-06-21/task-coverage.json",
              "line": 23,
              "category": "test coverage gap"
            }
