            {
              "message": "P1: `enabled` is not included in the canonical fingerprint, so two configs that differ only by opt-in state hash to the same `DryCheckConfigFingerprint`. `fingerprint_with_threshold` still encodes only `threshold`, `max_parallelism`, the reasoning-effort fields, and the known-bad percents ([config.rs:256-290]). Since `enabled` now changes whether the DRY gate is active, this omits a semantics-affecting field and can let stale coverage records survive an enable/disable flip without invalidation.",
