        {
          "type": "final",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "`resolve_dry_checker_config` reads `fast_reasoning_effort` / `final_reasoning_effort` from `AgentProfiles` and forwards them to `CodexDryChecker` without checking the allowed values. OS-06 says the loader intentionally leaves these strings untyped and the composition root remains the final allowed-values guard, while the downstream checker constructor just stores the strings and later passes them to `model_reasoning_effort`. This regresses the previous fail-closed validation path: an invalid profile value like `\"turbo\"` now reaches the Codex invocation instead of failing during wiring.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "apps/cli-composition/src/dry.rs",
              "line": 676,
              "category": "wiring stale to spec"
            }
          ],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:5f297852f15657d1cd3105edd821a57dc95c757058355efc45e1f19053e9043b",
          "at": "2026-06-21T11:46:13Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "final",
          "verdict": "zero_findings",
          "findings": [],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:1ebcf27d04876c13ab02e394d1c064e4808f60fbea3dd018ec9bcc7c9eb8b521",
          "at": "2026-06-21T11:50:05Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "fast",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "`AgentProfiles::load` now runs unconditionally before the `explicit_model` branch, so `dry_write` no longer preserves the existing explicit-override contract: a malformed or missing `.harness/config/agent-profiles.json` will fail the command even when `model: Some(...)` is supplied, and the existing `test_dry_write_explicit_model_bypasses_agent_profiles_resolution` will regress. If the D4 change is meant to keep explicit overrides independent, gate the profile load on `explicit_model.is_none()` or defer it until after the `items_dir` validation path.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "apps/cli-composition/src/dry/dry_checker_config.rs",
              "line": 66,
              "category": "regression"
            }
          ],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:91319110cc013da683a14c5769f20982c17cdedde9baf65155188df251b54dfc",
          "at": "2026-06-21T12:07:05Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "fast",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "`resolve_dry_checker_config` now short-circuits when `explicit_model` is set, so `dry_write --model ...` no longer loads `agent-profiles.json` for the `dry-checker` capability. That silently drops any configured `fast_reasoning_effort` / `final_reasoning_effort` and the associated validation, so the dry checker runs with the built-in defaults even when the profile explicitly requests different efforts.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "/home/flip451/individual/t-rust/templates/SoTOHE-core/apps/cli-composition/src/dry/dry_checker_config.rs",
              "line": 66,
              "category": "application logic in composition"
            }
          ],
